, quartered","500 g nopales cactus leaves, cut in pieces (see tip)","60 g water","1 tsp fine sea salt","400 g masa harina (e.g. Maseca, see tip)","400 g refried beans, tinned (see tip)","5 sprigs fresh coriander, leaves only, roughly chopped","250 g sour cream"]}],"id":"r401292","imageLink":"https:\/\/2.bp.blogspot.com\/-gSflox26q-A\/XZQFgjfAvtI\/AAAAAAAAbzk\/PSWRpvPxksImMCVmNdSTSLOpO4tMTy3rACLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_5ijtrNzmic4uQx4J.png","title":"Cactus Cornbreads (Sopes) and Chicken","publishedAt":"2018-11-03T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"47 g","fat":"14 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"66 g","calories":"2515 kJ \/ 599 kcal"},"usefulItems":"tea towel, tortilla maker, griddle pan, hob","hintsAndTricks":["To roast salsa ingredients, preheat oven to 160°C. Place ingredients on a baking tray, drizzle over olive oil and roast for <b>40-60 minutes<b> until soft and browned.","Panela is a fresh and smooth Mexican cheese. It is very soft and crumbly in texture and has some similarities with paneer or Cheshire cheese. It is available from Mexican supermarkets and online. If not available, substitute with cheese of choice.","Nopales are the thick, flat stems of the prickly pear cactus, eaten as a vegetable. The flavour of fresh nopales is like a mix of asparagus and French beans and they are chewy in texture. They are available from Mexican supermarkets or online.","Masa harina is a Mexican, gluten-free maize flour, traditionally used to make tortillas. It is available from Mexican supermarkets and online.","If a tortilla maker is not available, use a rolling pin to roll dough into discs (approx. <b>Ø 8 cm).<b>","To make your own <i>Refried Beans<\/i>, follow the recipe in the <i>Viva México<\/i> collection."],"basicInfo":["easy","40m","1h 10m","8 portions"]}